Text.SourceString: Oh, the new neighbor.//<portrait=happy>So, someone really <Italic>was</> moving into town, huh?//<portrait=normal>I couldn’t believe it until I saw you myself.
I don’t often go to the part of the island where your farm is.//<portrait=annoyed>It was overgrown the last time I visited. What a disaster.//How is it so far?
The salon is closed today, my dear. <NPCName>Erika</> is busy volunteering at the school.
Well, aren’t you a delight! Thank you for the compliment.//<portrait=normal>I quite like my hair today.
You can put some fruit and vegetables on a grill, then drizzle some honey over them for a fantastic, colorful meal!
The assorted grilled platter is my all-time favorite.
It’s crunchy and sweet.//<portrait=normal>Easy to toss after a long day of work.
There are wild mushrooms or berries by the park sometimes. I haven’t checked today, though.
<NPCName>Eva</> is a talented baker. She reminds me a lot of <NPCName>Betty</>.
Too bad <NPCName>Betty</> doesn’t bake anymore.//<portrait=normal>I do miss her pastries sometimes.
Remember to eat your greens, <PlayerName>$player</>.//The more color on your plate, the better.
I sound more and more nosy. I hope you don’t think I’m trying to police folks.
If <NPCName>Sam</> stops bringing in supplies from the mainland, maybe more people will start farming again.
I may talk to him about it, but I don’t know if that would be the right call…//<portrait=concerned>Probably not.

I may talk to him about it, but I don’t know if that would be the right call…//<portrait=concerned>Probably not.
You can put some fruit and vegetables on a grill, then drizzle some honey over them for a fantastic, colorful meal!
Inhale…exhale… I’m trying to relax a little.
You should take off your boots and be one with nature.//Take a deep breath…
You didn’t take off your boots.
Remember to eat your greens, <PlayerName>$player</>.//The more color on your plate, the better.
I sound more and more nosy. I hope you don’t think I’m trying to police folks.
<NPCName>Eva</> is a talented baker. She reminds me a lot of <NPCName>Betty</>.
Too bad <NPCName>Betty</> doesn’t bake anymore.//<portrait=normal>I do miss her pastries sometimes.
Sometimes we forget to consider the most important opinion when we make big decisions – our own.
It’s your voice that matters first, my dear. Then consider others.//Try not to get it confused. I know, I sometimes do.
I know this may sound random, but I just want to say that sometimes things don’t make sense, and that’s okay…//Oh, you’re so young and have so much life ahead of you.
What a charming prospect!
Stew is easy to make. It’s also impossible to mess up.//It was one of the first meals I learned to cook.
Have you tried your luck in the kitchen?
I feel like scavenging tomorrow.
Oh no! I have work tomorrow.//<portrait=concerned>Perhaps over the weekend. It’s better for running around the island.
Do you know who <NPCName>Lily</> reminds me of? Take a guess!//<portrait=happy>Oh my… This is fun.
YES! <NPCName>JIM</>! They look so alike.//<portrait=normal>The girl has her dad’s smile. Which is rare.
I know this may sound random, but I just want to say that sometimes things don’t make sense, and that’s okay…//Oh, you’re so young and have so much life ahead of you.
What a charming prospect!
The universe is so large. I don’t think we should try to understand everything.//<portrait=normal>Instead, we should strive for acceptance and contentment.
Acceptance… That one is hard to take in.
I prefer decor that has a meaningful story over something that’s brand new and clean looking.
That feels empty to me.//<portrait=happy>But of course, sometimes there are exceptions…
Do you know who <NPCName>Lily</> reminds me of? Take a guess!//<portrait=happy>Oh my… This is fun.
YES! <NPCName>JIM</>! They look so alike.//<portrait=normal>The girl has her dad’s smile. Which is rare.
We donate what we can to Starlet Town. Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> is very grateful.
Stew is easy to make. It’s also impossible to mess up.//It was one of the first meals I learned to cook.
Have you tried your luck in the kitchen?

Acceptance… That one is hard to take in.
Sometimes we forget to consider the most important opinion when we make crucial decisions – our own.
It’s your voice that matters first, my dear. Then consider others.//Try not to get it confused. I know, I sometimes do.
I feel like scavenging tomorrow. Maybe I’ll visit your farm on the way.
If that’s all right by you?//<portrait=normal>I don’t want to cross any boundaries or anything.
As the saying goes, “Sunday clears away the rust of the week.”//<portrait=normal>Oh! What a fun thing to say!
I believe that everything happens for a reason, be it good or bad.
Both good things and bad things, we learn from.
You can improve your cooking skills by watching the cooking channel… But they show reruns sometimes. That’s a bit of a bummer, especially when you’re looking forward to a new recipe.
I suppose if you miss an episode, it’s good that they rerun it.
I don’t shop much at Socket. It’s not my taste.

I don’t shop much at Socket. It’s not my taste.
My hair is my signature, you know. I have been wearing it like this since I was a bachelorette.
Goodness knows, it was a long time ago. I tried growing it out a bit one time, but it’s just not me.
I collect many things… Antique furniture, for example. I’m always in the market for that.
<NPCName>Ben</> has a stunning collection. Though you’ll never know when he has something new. Hmm…

<NPCName>Sam</> and I are going out dancing at the Tavern tomorrow night. You should join us!
Oh, I hope <NPCName>Theo</> is there! He has such a fabulous voice!

Oh my, I need to get my hair done. I can’t possibly go out like this!
My hairspray doesn’t hold all day… I should write the company and let them know. What a disaster!
Ah, you’d think it would be easier for us to get the groceries we need, what with owning a general store and all.
It’s easier for us than the general public, true…//But still, we rely a lot on local gardeners like you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
I went to check for some shallots out back near the lake yesterday. But nothing. Maybe I should check again today and see if they’ve sprouted.
<NPCName>Sam</>’s in the mood for fried rice, and it isn’t the same without fresh shallots.//<portrait=concerned>If you ever make it yourself, you’ll agree with me.

It’s easier for us than the general public, true…//But still, we rely a lot on local gardeners like you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Oh my! I can do with a little rain right now.//The heat is destroying my hair!
Ah, I’m being dramatic again. I think I’ll cool off and have some ice cream or something.//<portrait=annoyed>The heat is making me fuzzy.
Are you ready for snow season? The kids are going to love it. //<portrait=happy>They usually gather in that park over there, building snowmen. Ah!
I hope Winter isn’t as cold this year.//<portrait=normal>I can’t seem to find my wool gloves anywhere.

I hope Winter isn’t as cold this year.//<portrait=normal>I can’t seem to find my wool gloves anywhere.
You know, <PlayerName>$player</>, I’m going to complain less as part of my New Year’s resolution.//I have an excellent feeling about next year!
The key is to find more activities to keep myself busy.//<portrait=normal>The less free time I have, the less I’ll have to complain about. You should try that.
I might go to the lake later. Rainy days are perfect for berry hunting.//Can you guess why?
Less competition, correct! Great minds think alike, they say.
You don’t mind the rain, I see.
I really should rest… I’m starting to feel sleepy.
How about the rain, huh? How are we supposed to go on like this?
Ah, I’m being dramatic.
Storming again? Seriously, how are we going to survive this Winter if the sun keeps hiding like this?
I just wish there was something we could do to help.
You don’t mind the storm, I see.
What a storm, huh?//How are we supposed to go on like this?
Ah, I’m being dramatic.
How’s your Winter so far? I hope the cold and the mountain of snow doesn’t put you off.
Snowing again? Seriously, how are we going to survive this Winter if the sun keeps hiding like this?
I just wish there was something we could do to help.
You don’t mind the snow, I see.
We mix the dyes here ourselves. All organic, without any harsh chemicals.
Gosh, I sound like a salesperson. Ha ha!
<NPCName>Erika</> and I don’t have set customers, per se.//But customers usually have a preference for who they want to work on their hair.
Business is going okay at the farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I have to mention this before I forget.//<portrait=normal>I felt that you would visit today, for some odd reason… I’m glad you did. My instinct never fails me.
I have a bit of free time this morning, before errands.
It’s become a habit of mine to wind down with a cup of green tea after a long day of work.
My gut tells me that today is going to be a relaxing day.
Something told me to come here.
Maybe it’s the greenery that my eyes are longing for, lately.//<portrait=normal>My body is craving some nature.
I’m going to take it easy and eat only raw food today.
Don’t you think a boutique hotel type thing would do splendidly here?
It’s too nice of a day to stay inside, isn’t it?
No, I’m not a diver… But you go ahead! I'm a Sagittarius, you know... Fire and water don't mix.
Though, you probably need to go to the other side of the island to dive.
I have to read for half an hour or so before going to bed. It’s become a habit, I think…//I can’t just close my eyes and fall asleep.
I have mixed feelings about putting a TV in our bedroom.//I feel like it might be too much of a distraction.
That’s a very good point. It is convenient.
Oh, you should have seen this place! This was overgrown before Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> decided to bring everybody together to clean it up a bit.
And look how pretty it is now. Islanders can come here and have a picnic.
I filled a basket full of wild fruit and flowers… There were plenty near the shrine, over there.
Have you found any flowers? Oh dear… I sure hope I didn’t pick all of the flowers. There were plenty of them left, earlier.
It’s too nice of a day to stay inside, isn’t it?

Your farm was neglected for a long time. You should have seen it! It wasn’t a pretty sight.//Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> was going to turn your grandparents’ farm into a community garden before you moved in.
I’m glad you did, by the way. Now someone will take care of the land.
Can I get you anything?
*busily arranging shelves*
I have to go to work soon. Let me just finish up with this shelf.
This sauce is delicious! I wonder what <NPCName>Frank</> puts in it.
The cups could use a little chilling before serving. Then it would be just right.
Do I talk to <NPCName>Noah</> or <NPCName>Frank</> about this? Who’s in charge in here tonight?
They need to increase the volume a bit, don’t you think, <PlayerName>$player</>?
